                            <comment id="134470" author="adilger" created="Tue, 24 Nov 2015 23:17:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I suspect that this is still the same problem as &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-7222&quot; title=&quot;conf-sanity test_84: invalid llog tail at log id 0x4:10/0 offset 16384&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-7222&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-7222&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, due to the &quot;&lt;tt&gt;llog_process_thread()) invalid length 0 in llog record for index 0/68&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; message, just a slightly different form of corrupt llog.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
